      <Nspectrum>
------------------------------------------------------------------------
--- Spectra and mean energy values of prompt neutrons                ---
... in cm system of the fissioning nucleus.                          ---
--- pre-saddle, between saddle and scission and from fragments       ---
--- after emssion of DN neutrons and DZ protons.                     ---
------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
The energy values mark the lower limit of the corresponding energy bins:
e.g  channel '0.1 MeV' contains the spectrum between 0.1 and 0.2 MeV.
The dmp folder provides spectra with 1 keV resolution.
The spectrum of pre-saddle neutrons is calculated with a different
number of events than the saddle-scission or post-scission values.
In the following table, the counts of this spectrum are up- or down-scaled
in order to make the spectra comparable.
 
